00:38:56.440 --> 00:38:59.160
I can tell you the typical
traditional publishing

00:38:59.160 --> 00:39:01.270
route, as it used
to be especially,

00:39:01.270 --> 00:39:04.480
and can still be today, is
it starts with query letters

00:39:04.480 --> 00:39:05.060
to agents.

00:39:05.060 --> 00:39:08.930
You write maybe 30 to 40
to 50 and get rejected

00:39:08.930 --> 00:39:10.820
that amount of times minus one.

00:39:10.820 --> 00:39:13.530
And then that agent says
that they will represent you,

00:39:13.530 --> 00:39:16.030
and then they query all the
publishing houses, and they get

00:39:16.030 --> 00:39:17.439
rejected all but one time.

00:39:17.439 --> 00:39:19.230
And those are the two
parties that you then

00:39:19.230 --> 00:39:22.070
need to split all of the
royalties with later on.

00:39:22.070 --> 00:39:24.155
Those parties can change
anything about your book

00:39:24.155 --> 00:39:24.780
that they want.

00:39:24.780 --> 00:39:25.863
They can change the title.

00:39:25.863 --> 00:39:27.072
They can create the cover.

00:39:27.072 --> 00:39:28.530
