00:41:38.880 --> 00:41:42.890
But other than that, I wrote 350
personal emails asking people

00:41:42.890 --> 00:41:44.490
hey, what's going on with you?

00:41:44.490 --> 00:41:45.410
I just wrote a book.

00:41:49.060 --> 00:41:50.060
SEEMA VASHI: Yes, Henry?

00:41:50.060 --> 00:41:54.144
AUDIENCE: So from finishing
a first draft, what

00:41:54.144 --> 00:41:55.310
was the timeline from there?

00:41:55.310 --> 00:41:56.110
How many drafts?

00:41:56.110 --> 00:41:58.190
How long did it
take to get to this?

00:41:58.190 --> 00:41:59.398
LAUREN EPSHTEYN: Interesting.

00:41:59.398 --> 00:42:01.540
OK, so my process of
writing, personally,

00:42:01.540 --> 00:42:07.660
is I edit constantly and
frequently as I'm writing.

00:42:07.660 --> 00:42:09.910
So there was never
a time where I just

00:42:09.910 --> 00:42:12.450
had one full draft unedited.

00:42:12.450 --> 00:42:14.810
I had gone back and
really done so much of it

00:42:14.810 --> 00:42:17.200
as I was going
chapter by chapter.

00:42:17.200 --> 00:42:21.020
But I finished a first
draft, so to speak,

00:42:21.020 --> 00:42:22.340
in February of this year.

00:42:22.340 --> 00:42:25.470
And then I sent it off
to a professional editor,

00:42:25.470 --> 00:42:27.260
who I note in the
acknowledgements.

00:42:27.260 --> 00:42:28.580
I thought I had it
in pretty good shape.

00:42:28.580 --> 00:42:29.913
I'd read through it a few times.

00:42:29.913 --> 00:42:32.460
She caught over 4,000
little typos or changes

00:42:32.460 --> 00:42:33.590
that she wanted make.

00:42:33.590 --> 00:42:37.830
She missed about seven,
but that's another story.

00:42:37.830 --> 00:42:42.280
And that took about-- she sent
those back to me mid-June.

00:42:42.280 --> 00:42:45.470
I did another full read through
and made a couple more changes,

00:42:45.470 --> 00:42:47.540
and then sent it off
to the publisher,

00:42:47.540 --> 00:42:50.030
the final publication,
in the beginning of July.

00:42:50.030 --> 00:42:51.640
So it really wasn't that long.

00:42:51.640 --> 00:42:54.680
But then again, I had
spent years, at least

00:42:54.680 --> 00:42:57.290
the last two,
solidly both writing,

00:42:57.290 --> 00:42:59.347
but really editing as I went.

00:42:59.347 --> 00:43:00.720
Yeah, good question.

00:43:00.720 --> 00:43:03.460
SEEMA VASHI: When did you know
